# OpenShift sample installation

*Note*: This page is not meant to be used as public documentation. It is simply
meant to describe the sample files in this folder.

These samples assume that you have access to the following users:

1. system:admin (or a user who has cluster-admin privileges)
2. developer

You must also have an OpenShift project created called "operator-example"

### Setup

As the system:admin user install the following files:

crd.yaml
cluster-role-sa.yaml
cluster-role-user.yaml
role-binding-sa.yaml
role-binding-user.yaml
service-account.yaml

This will allow the developer user to create and run the operator in the
"operator-example" project as well as create and delete Couchbase clusters. The
operator and first cluster can be created by installing the following files into
your Kubernetes cluster with the developer user.

operator.yaml
secret.yaml
couchbase-cluster.yaml